                  <history>
                    <origin>
                      <origDate notBefore="1800" notAfter="1899"/>                            
                        Several names are mentioned throughout the manuscript, in the main hand or in a later hand.
                        The name of <persName role="owner" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14664WalattaHe">Walatta Ḥǝywat</persName>, still legible on <locus target="#30r"/>, was replaced
                        by that of <persName role="owner" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14665WalattaMa">Walatta Māryām</persName> in the supplication on <locus target="#31r"/>.
                        Other individuals involved with the manuscript, and possibly owners, are mentioned in the <ref target="#a1">scribal supplication</ref> on <locus target="#36v"/>:
                        <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14666WaldaKr">Walda Krǝstos</persName>, 
                        <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14667AbKalla">ʾAb Kallalā</persName>, <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14668TasfaYo">Tasfā Yoḥannǝs</persName>, 
                        <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14669GabraEg">Gabra ʾƎgziʾabǝḥer</persName>, <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14670WalattaSa">Walatta Sanbat</persName>.
                    </origin>
                    <provenance>According to the account on the manuscripts’ provenance given by Eugène Tisserant, this manuscript is among those
                      acquired by <persName role="owner" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4805Grebaut">Sylvain Grébaut</persName> in <date when="1925"/> with funds of
                      <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14055SaintJ">Jean Saint</persName>. 
                      The manuscripts originated from Šawā (ʾAddis ʾAbabā, Dabra Libānos, Dabra Bǝrhān),
                      Goǧǧām (Dimā Giyorgis, Marṭula Māryām, Dabra Warq) and Bagemdǝr (Gondar, ʾAzazo Takla Hāymānot) and very few from Tǝgrāy.
                    </provenance>
                    <acquisition when="1928">The manuscript entered the library on <date>18 April 1928</date>.</acquisition>
                  </history>
